Dear All,

I would like to communicate some information on the "Cahiers".

1. Last year, prompted by several people, in particular Ronnie, I had =20
asked for the inclusion of the "Cahiers" in the ISI database, and I =20
was informed that the assessment process required about 1 year. The =20
answer arrived in August: it is rejected. As I was surprised, all the =20
more since I thought TAC had been accepted, I asked for the reasons. I =20
join the answer at the end of this msg.

2. The "Cahiers" show that a journal need not be very expensive. It =20
costs 82 euros a year, and lives on its subscriptions (almost all by =20
foreign universities) which entirely and exactly cover the expenses: =20
printing of the final pdf file which I give to the (commercial) =20
printer, envelopes and stamps I use for snail mail delivery.
It should be noted that there is no staff expenses since, without any =20
financial nor material support, I myself edit the complete file (with =20
the help of the authors who kindly comply with my format =20
requirements?), and manage the subscriptions, the packing up and =20
sending of the volumes.

I am sorry of the ThomasReuters decision  which might be a prejudice =20
for the authors, I'll try to have it reversed in the future if it is =20
possible, and I hope you all will help me.

Kind regards
Andree

