Sujet:  =09RE: Cahiers de Topologie et Geometrie Differentielle Categoriques


Dear Prof. Ehresmann,

Among the many criteria we use to evaluate a journal for possible =20
inclusion in the database, a journal's citation record (how often the =20
journal is cited and which journals cite it and are cited by it) is =20
one of the more important considerations.  We examined the citation =20
record of the Cahiers for both 2009 and 2010. (The 2010 citation data =20
became available just a few months ago).  The citation data for both =20
years show that the citation rate for the Cahiers was very low - even =20
lower in 2010 than in 2009 - and did not compare favorably with other =20
core mathematics journals indexed in the database, in particular, =20
journals covering the subject areas of topology and category.

Theory and Applications of Categories was indeed added to the database =20
earlier this year and during its evaluation demonstrated a much =20
stronger citation rate.  Many high impact journals covering the field =20
of topology, such as Topology and Its Applications, Topology and =20
Topological Methods in Nonlinear Analysis, are also indexed in the =20
database. Thus, these fields in mathematics are well represented in =20
the database.

We would be pleased to arrange a reevaluation of the journal in 36 =20
months, if you care to contact us again at that time.  (In the =20
meantime, it is not necessary to send us further issues.)  Further =20
exposure to the research community, new quantitative data and our =20
evolving coverage priorities may yield a different decision.

Sincerely,

Rodney Chonka
Editor, Physical, Chemical & Earth Sciences
Thomson  Reuters




